originalText.text: My experience with Leslie has been nothing short of amazing. I started dealing with intermittent hip/ankle pain for the last 7/8 years that had recently become more chronic. I tried numerous approaches for relief (PT, acupuncture, etc.) and was recommended MFR by a family member. I felt significant relief after the first 2/3 appointments, and am at a point where 80-100% of relief is achievable if I stay consistent with recommended maintenance and check-ins. Leslie in deeply knowledgeable, encouraging, and listens with an open and helpful mind. I highly recommend her and trying MFR if other approaches to pain relief have fallen short of expectations.

originalText.text: Leslie helped me with chronic pain from a physical trauma I experienced over 15 years ago as well as provided care to my cesarean scar from my birth 19 months ago. I came to her in my efforts to prepare my body preconceptually and after our sessions she not only helped me with my physical concerns but also my emotional self. She is gentle, kind, knowledgeable and very supportive. After every session I felt more youthful and energetic! I feel much more like my prepregnancy self and am so glad I dedicated time and money to do this for myself. I highly recommend Leslie!

originalText.text: Leslie Daley is what you hope every health care practitioner would be like. I came to her with reoccurring pelvic pain, and with her empathy, skilled touch, and ability to see the whole picture, finally felt listened to after so many months of confusion and unease— that resounding “yes!” moment of symptom relief and of hope. Leslie has a keen ability to navigate more sensitive topics around pelvic pain, and with a gentle though intentional touch. She helps you feel like a true participant in your own healing, while gently guiding you with insight and care. I can not recommend her enough. An OT worth celebrating!

originalText.text:
Leslie is an extremely knowledgeable professional who listens intently to what my symptoms are and treats them not just individually, but holistically. She hears each symptom out, and connects them to the body as a whole, but also to me as the patient in how those symptoms are affecting me and the things I want or need to do. It's an invaluable and rare skill to find in a healthcare professional, and I'm profoundly appreciative.
I came to Leslie with lots of aches and pains and slowly, I'm noticing more and more of them creep away and not return. I would (and have!) recommended her services to friends and loved ones. Leslie offers a unique and important patient experience, and results have been truly palpable for me, especially after other more conventional methods have failed.
I cannot recommend her highly enough.

originalText.text: Working with Leslie has released half a decade's chronic pain in my lower-back and leg.  She is intuitive and caring in her approach and has given me the tools and means to care for myself and improve how I feel and function with my body.   This is the best myofascial release work I've ever had and am really glad to have found it!   Great location too with a clean and convenient studio.
